      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BLUE LABUBU (6) boasts a strong record this journey with six wins and four minors from 13 tries. Placed last time (21.95) at Ballarat in a Grade 5, finishing second and beaten one length. Has the ability and looks a key chance here. SOLICIT (1) flew the lids with a fast early split last time, hitting the frame with a 0.8 lengths second (22.14) over 390m at this track and making it two placings on end. Form from his last run is proving to be solid. Will give a great sight again. ESSENCE (2) had been racing well prior to her last start fourth at this track following a Free For All win three back with a third placing. Well placed here and should do much better. SCOTT GREYSCALE (3) was below best last time at Bendigo (24.09) in a Grade 5, finishing a 4.5 lengths fifth. Boasts a top strike-rate from this draw, winning three of five runs.",
